reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Took me a while to buy this as I was busy reading all the 1-2 star reviews and their concerns. Luckily mine was great and didn't have any of the issues (leaking, peeling paint, etc). However, I do have issues with the knobs as they are hard to turn counter-clockwise, they are NOT like the knob of regular kitchen stove-top knob where you can turn easily. (or maybe I'm supposed to press in then turn, I have to verify that.) I just feel like one day the plastic knob is going to break. Until then Mr. Plier will always be a reach away.As for the burner, it burns high, and boils water/cook quicker than the inside burner (very old). Food now tasted like they're being cooked.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Stay clear of this camping stove.
reviews.reviewText: I would give this 0 stars if I could. I bought this specifically for canning. I have canned on other camping stoves previously, but wanted one that wasn't so old. It was easy to assemble and sturdy enough, although fairly cheap looking. However, from the first time it was turned on to use it had an extremely loud hissing type sound, as if it was putting off excessive amounts of heat at the burner. We triple checked that the regulator and hose were correctly assembled. The noise continued, but we used it to can anyways, figuring it was just loud. I canned a total of 4 hours over a couple weeks and it completely drained my new propane tank. I never turned it on more than the lowest setting and it still heated up crazy fast. I made sure to close the valves and shut off the stove after each use. Obviously it has a flaw somewhere or leak because my propane should NOT have drained after only 4 hours on the lowest setting. I also did not like the paint smell during the first use, or the paint that peeled on the outside of the wind guards because of the dangerously high heat put off when on the lowest setting. I would be scared to try this on the high settings. Unfortunately I bought this during the summer, but didn't start canning until the fall, so it is too late for me to return. This is useless to me. I wish I could get a refund, and I will be sure to steer any family and friends away from buying this camping stove.

Product arrived in a timely manner, haven't set it up yet. We are going to use it to boil sap in the spring.. product looks very solid and we'll build. Brother purchased one also and he is very happy with it.

reviews.reviewTitle: Burn off the paint ahead of time.
reviews.reviewText: This burner sells for 800+ usd on another site. I ordered a used one and can not see when or if it was ever used. This is a fantastic item for the deck. I got mine for 150 cdn. I can sear steaks now. But, you need to bring it up to high heat and burn off the toxic paint from the grills. Otherwise the smell will ruin your food. Put a griddle on top and crank it high.
Great for camping trips or to use in the back yard to do seafood boils.

Bought this product just over a month ago, was excited to use it. Went to light it and the front of it flashed at me, the front gas Adjusters caught fire. I had to put out a fire.... nearly set my deck on fire. Decided to water and soap test it. SURE ENOUGH, leaking in 2 separate areas. Really disappointed, I have 2 Coleman stoves that never have done anything like this. The burners are either 100%-10% very little adjustment. OVERPRICED JUNK. This is now at my work in the scrap metal pile. BUYER BEWARE, fire hazard. There's a reason they don't accept returns.
